president bush is popular among a majority of 
blacks according to a cbs newsthe new york times poll released 
thursday 
bush has an approval rating of 56 percent among blacks far 
exceeding the 13 percent approval blacks gave his predecessor when 
president reagan was in office about the same amount of time the 
cbs evening news reported 
in may 1982 when reagan had a 73 percent disapproval rate among 
blacks while the current poll indicated that 26 percent of blacks 
disapproved of bush said kathy frankovic of the networks polling 
division 
cbstimes polls conducted during reagans entire time in office 
found that he had an average 67 percent disapproval rate among 
blacks frankovic said 
for the last 30 years five out of six blacks have voted for the 
democratic presidential candidate no matter who the nominee was 
but cbs said thursdays poll indicated that 9 percent of blacks 
would vote for bush if an election were held today while an 
additional 20 percent said they would wait to see who the 
democratic nominee was before deciding 
the current poll of 403 blacks was conducted between march 30 
and april 2 and had a margin of error of plus or minus 5 percentage 
points 
