policy as politically and marketing motivated 
august felando ata president said the move was devastating 
for the us tuna fleet basically we have now lost our market 
the eastern pacific is the most productive area in the world for 
yellowfin tuna fishing and its our traditional grounds he said 
us boats will be forced to other fisheries or even go 
out of business while foreign boats will sell their tuna to 
nonus buyers felando added 
starkists new policy was aimed at purse seine net fishing in 
the eastern pacific ocean because it is the only fishery where 
dolphin swim with tuna the nets are intentionally dropped below 
schools of dolphins to capture the tuna underneath when a 
drawstring is pulled to close the net 
but the company said it also would continue to refuse to buy 
fish caught anywhere with gill or driftnets 
gill or driftnets are set on the water overnight and trap 
anything fish birds and other marine life that enters the area 
covered by the net 
experts say most of the approximately 2 million tons of tuna 
caught worldwide each year is caught in purse sein nets without 
snaring dolphins ten percent is caught using driftnets or 
encircling dolphins in purse sein nets 
the united states the only country that regulates dolphin 
mortality in connection with fishing allows a maximum of 20500 
deaths and stations observers on board all usflagged vessels to 
verify the number of deaths 
