the missile and its basing with a goal of initial operation in 
1997 458 million for six additional research and development 
missiles and 87 million for inflation 
the estimated cost of the multiplewarhead mx nuclear missile 
dropped 39 billion from 23 billion primarily because of a 
reduction in the number of planned missiles from 255 to 193 the 
drop was partially offset by revised inflation rates with an 
estimated increase of 236 million 
the estimates consist of the annual costs of research and 
development purchase of the weapon itself and associated 
construction added together for the several years each weapon will 
be bought sometimes extending into the next century cost of 
operations such as fuel and crew wages are not included 
the arleigh burkeclass destroyer or ddg51 increased 4 
billion from a previous estimate of 28 billion the navy cited an 
increase in the number of ships from 33 to 38 and revised inflation 
rates as the reasons for the 15 percent jump 
the other navy program the defense secretary may curtail the 
ssn21 seawolf attack submarine dropped in estimated cost from 
20 billion to 16 billion because of a decrease in the number of 
submarines from 12 to nine 
the estimated cost of the c17 cargo plane increased 44 
billion from a previous price of 374 billion the air force 
blamed the rise on inflation and schedule changes due to plans to 
stretch out the program 
slower production rates frequently raise total costs by reducing 
production efficiency 
one of the largest increases in army programs was in the medium 
tactical vehicles in which the estimated cost jumped from 86 
billion to 161 billion or 88 percent 
the army attributed the rise to an increase in the number of 
trucks from 79157 to 102322 an extension of the modernization 
program from 15 to 30 years schedule changes and inflation 
the estimated cost of the m1 tank program which cheney has 
proposed canceling in the budget for the fiscal year beginning oct 
1 dropped 6 billion due to a decrease in the number of tanks 
