an iowa environmental official says hes 
waiting for a federal agency to accept its moral responsibility 
for selling off 12755 bushels of corn it knew was contaminated 
with a deadly toxin 
the mound of grain is believed to have the highest concentration 
of cancercausing aflatoxin ever found in this country as much as 
1600 times the maximum allowable limit for human consumption 
state and federal officials say 
an order thursday from the iowa division of environmental 
protection gave the farmers home administration and the pruess 
elevator co of lowden until april 20 to remove the corn and held 
them equally liable 
