toles 38 grew up in suburban hamburg his father was the 
business editor of the buffalo times until it folded in 1939 but 
toles said he never planned to go into journalism much less 
cartooning 
i drew as a kid every kid draws but i never took an art 
lesson he said 
toles was a staff artist for the campus newspaper at the state 
university of new york at buffalo he was hired in 1973 as a 
graphic artist at the nowdefunct buffalo courierexpresss 
he initially did caricatures and other illustrative work but 
found his vocation when douglas l turner then the papers editor 
asked him to do an editorial cartoon one day 
since toles joined the buffalo news when the courierexpress 
folded in 1982 his work has been syndicated nationally by 
universal press syndicate and he was a finalist for the 1985 
pulitzer in editorial cartooning 
a cover story in the washington journalism review in december 
1988 called toles the rodney dangerfield of editorial 
cartooning because he was wellrespected in the profession but 
not well known nationally 
