cambodian guerrilla leader prince 
norodom sihanouk said today he left his new home inside cambodia on 
the advice of thai officials after heavy shelling by government 
forces 
the prince denied he intended to flee sereipheap which he 
declared his home in february the village is in a part of 
northwestern cambodia the guerrillas call liberated zones 
in reality it was my thai escorts who decided to take me by 
car to surin he said 
the prince issued the statement in response to a british 
broadcasting corp report which said he suffered a humiliating 
defeat in wedensdays attack by government troops 
sihanouk said that on thursday he received a letter from thai 
deputy prime minister and minister of defense gen chavalit 
yongchaiyudh saying he was deeply concerned about the princes 
security 
