phnom penh units in the area will continue to harass the 
village with longrange weapons which is certainly not safe for 
you and your family to go back to at the moment 
chavalit said sihanouk should remain in thailand until the 
situation improved and the thai government would provide him with 
security the guerrilla leader said 
the bangkok post said the shelling began near sereipheap early 
wednesday and sihanouk and his wife princess monique and other 
family members were evacuated about midday 
at first they took shelter in bunkers in the village because the 
attack was not expected to intensify the report said 
they were later moved to a safe location in thailand after 
leaving most of their belongings in cambodia the report said the 
other 700 villagers were evacuated at the same time and there were 
no casualties the report said 
sereipheap literally means freedom village in the khmer 
language the prince who heads the threefaction guerrilla 
alliance fighting the vietnameseinstalled government returned to 
cambodia to boost the morale of his fighters 
sihanouk backed by the united states last fled cambodia when 
vietnamese troops invaded the country in late 1978 he lived for 
the next 11 years in exile dividing his time between china 
france north korea and thailand 
