5354 billion it was the largest increase in seven months all of 
the strength came in manufacturing the sector of the economy that 
had been most affected by sluggishness resulting from the federal 
reserve boards high interest rate policy 
in january business sales rose 04 percent enough to stay 
ahead of the 03 percent increase in inventories 
i think the economy is picking up a little steam and well see 
a decent first half said economist david berson of the federal 
national mortgage association 
he and other analysts view the combination of surging sales and 
falling inventories is a sign of strength a sharp buildup in 
inventories can lead to a recession retailers and wholesalers with 
too many goods stop ordering more in response factories cut 
production and lay off workers 
the february activity sharply reduced the ratio of business 
inventories to sales to 148 down from 151 in january that means 
it would take 148 months to exhaust inventories at the february 
sales pace 
that suggests as much as anything that this economy has 
skirted a recession said economist james annable of first 
national bank of chicago 
