<TEXT>
alberto fujimori a softspoken agricultural 
engineer who enjoys growing rosebushes in his backyard has 
suddenly become the man most likely to take the helm of peru one 
of latin americas most ungovernable nations 
the 51yearold japanese peruvian came out of nowhere in 
sundays presidential election to rob a majority from novelist 
mario vargas llosa and force him into a runoff 
pollsters say the centrist independents popularity is growing 
daily as vargas llosas support declines with the likely support 
of leftist parties in a june runoff fujimori appears unbeatable 
the lima press dubbed his rise the fujimori phenomenon 
headlines told of vargas llosa getting swept away by a tsunami 
a tidal wave of fujimania 
imagine the inability of these political parties to manage an 
electoral campaign it makes me laugh that theyve come out looking 
so ridiculous fujimori said in an interview with the associated 
press one of his first since the election 
he compared his campaign strategy to the martial arts you 
take advantage of the forces of the other boom boom wherever they 
lead he said slicing his hand through an imaginary brick 
vargas llosa also an independent and his rightofcenter 
democratic front coalition spent more than 36 million on his 
campaign according to the respected news magazine caretas 
fujimori who sold a house his car and a tractor to raise 
campaign funds spent about 180000 
he claims to be the only candidate truly independent of 
professional politicians but he has shown political skill 
which some say he honed during his years as a university rector in 
a country where universities are highly politicized 
in the early days of his campaign he posed for photographers 
dressed as a samurai warrior and a karate expert he said it was 
necessary to get attention 
within days after sundays vote vargas llosa was meeting with 
advisers and pondering his political future at a friends beach 
home south of lima he reportedly considered dropping out of the 
race 
fujimori meanwhile was attending to the pack of reporters 
camped in front of his middleclass lima home posing for pictures 
with some chinese squash and handing out flowers from his garden 
fujimori has avoided specifics throughout his sixmonth 
campaign speaking instead of broad social goals like improved 
health care and revitalizing industry 
analysts say fujimoris success was due to voters alarm over 
vargas llosas explicit plan for drastic austerity measures and 
their wariness of the oldtime politicians in the democratic front 
fujimori is one of five children and the oldest son of japanese 
immigrants who came to peru in 1934 from the city of kumamoto on 
the southern japanese island of kyushu 
his father worked at various jobs including an upholstery shop 
he opened in downtown lima the family lost the business during a 
boycott of japanese businesses during world war ii 
fujimori earned a degree in agricultural engineering from the 
national agrarian university in 1960 and later served as the 
schools rector from 1984 to 1989 he has studied in france 
belgium and the united states he speaks spanish japanese 
english french and german 
though his parents were buddhists fujimori grew up a catholic 
in this overwhelmingly catholic country 
he doesnt mind if people view him as smart honest and 
hardworking because he is japanese but he says hes 100 percent 
peruvian and has only an ancestral connection to japan 
he describes himself as studious introverted without any 
common vices and says working is his hobby he works 12 to 13 
hours a day and refuses to eat or drink anything between meals i 
dont want to be distracted he said 
usually dressed in a threepiece suit fujimori appears stiff 
and serious when he meets with the public but voters have warmed 
to him and his promises of discipline and hard work 
he says his political movement called simply change 90 is an 
expression of people who are tired of the old corrupt political 
parties and who just want to work 
fujimori has support in perus growing evangelical community 
whose leaders see in him the simple honest president the country 
needs one of his two vicepresidential candidates is carlos 
garcia a baptist pastor the other is maximo san roman a bread 
factory owner who has perfected ways of making bread from carrots 
and sweet potatoes 
