<TEXT>
it wont be in time for this easter but an 
agriculture department scientist says people one day will be able 
to buy blooming lilies throughout the year 
horticulturist mark s roh of the departments agricultural 
research service said a special treatment has been developed which 
brings a lily from a very small bulb to bloom in about 280 days 
instead of two to three years and in living colors not just 
traditional white 
he said the hybrid lily colors include red creamy yellow and 
bright lavender flowers on 12 to 25inch stems 
the new procedure bypasses the field production of lilies 
altogether allowing them to undergo forced controlled growth in 
greenhouses to reduce major viruses and soilborne fungal diseases 
that plague fieldgrown lilies 
roh said in a report by the agency that he plans to formally 
release the hybrid lilies to nurseries this year 
when the method is commercialized a company would probably 
offer the treated bulbils or small bulbs to nurseries that would 
in turn produce potted plants or cut flowers for consumers the 
report said 
us growers sold more than 9 million potted lilies in 1988 at a 
wholesale value of more than 34 million according to the most 
recent usda figures 
