and the socialists 33 seats 
the democratic forum emphasizes hungarian tradition and 
christian values and favors the introduction of market forces into 
hungarys socialist economy at a gradual pace to soften the effects 
of inflation and unemployment 
the second strongest party the free democrats was formed by 
former leading dissidents and campaigned for rapid economic 
changes the party won 96 seats and will most likely head the 
opposition 
