<TEXT>
lifting a slender 5foothigh cross before him 
pope john paul ii led a torchlight procession through the colosseum 
friday night to reenact jesus march to his crucifixion 
thousands of people bearing candles in red paper cones watched 
the good friday ceremony broadcast to millions throughout the 
world 
the ceremony was one of several worldwide that marked good 
friday thousands of pilgrims retraced the traditional procession 
route through jerusalems old city and hundreds of thousands of 
roman catholics turned out for the 146th annual reenactment of the 
crucifixion at an ancient indian ceremonial site in mexico 
in the philippines more than 20 filipino penitents were nailed 
to crosses today and others whipped themselves bloody as asias 
only predominantly christian nation marked the crucifixion the 
