roy benjamin would like to send hundreds of 
thousands of books each month to the soviet union and the nations 
of eastern europe where he believes there is a huge market for 
them 
benjamin is a publisher so you might think this just makes good 
sense just as it makes sense for example to hundreds of american 
companies with consumer goods or manufactured products to sell 
but his plan is very different he would donate his skills and 
time the books would be gifts he believes those who finance the 
idea those who read the books and the nations involved would be 
the better for it 
in his 73 years benjamin has learned that while good ideas are 
appreciated ideas backed by a practical plan of implementation are 
worth a hundred times more and so he has done the preliminary work 
his proposal international friendship books has been 
reviewed in publishing circles shown to the us government 
officials and tested directly on officials of the european nations 
that would benefit 
the responses have been uniformly good rita klimova 
czechoslovakian amabassador to the united states told him that the 
people of her country yearn for books that will tell the american 
story 
as chairman of the benjamin co based in elmsford ny roy 
benjamin has helped create hundreds of titles and tens of millions 
of books many of them under cooperative arrangements with 
corporations 
he is widely connected in publishing circles and experienced in 
bringing various groups together a requirement of the program he 
proposes these are the basics 
distribution of 100000 to 500000 or more copies of a single 
selected title each quarter eventually monthly through foreign 
schools colleges libraries education groups and other 
organizations 
government agencies or book distribution organizations in the 
recipient countries would be responsible for seeing that books 
reach the selected organizations 
a second phase sending selfcontained libraries or sets of 
books to business professional and political leaders it was added 
when he found professional organizations lacked basic texts even 
roberts rules of order 
american corporations would underwrite costs of the books 
their investment to be justified by the marketing and public 
relations dividends their sponsorship would deliver 
what a great way for american companies to become known in the 
new market economies of europe he muses contemplating how they 
might benefit from a simple notation on the rear cover 
compliments of xyz company for example 
foundations us government agencies associations and other 
groups might participate as joint sponsors 
title selection would be made by a board comprised of us 
publishers editors educators librarians and government 
officials educators and publishers in selected foreign countries 
might also make suggestions 
administration and development would be through a 
notforprofit organization perhaps international friendship 
books inc that benjamin is ready to develop and direct 
for benjamin the idea isnt new for years he has traveled the 
world and wherever he went the idea was nurtured earlier he had 
hoped to develop the plan for china and india but scarcity of us 
products there delayed him 
when eastern europes socialist nations decided on market 
economies rather than economies dictated centrally by communist 
officials the idea became more urgent 
much depends on the cooperation of us companies but benjamin 
thinks hell get it why first as media books are one of the 
few games in town he says in eastern europe he explains 
access to conventional advertising is either nonexistent or 
severely limited 
next he says books are highly revered and respected by these 
people read and reread passed on to others and read again 
theyre never discarded 
its a rare situation in which everyone seems to win benjamin 
a well trophied golfer who spends many hours on the course and who 
still must work at his own business says he isnt afraid of the 
added task 
he says simply id like to repay some of the dividends and 
fulfillment my work has given me over the years 
