what do you do with an obsolete border 
guardhouse especially if its right downtown turn it into a 
tourist office says a veteran us army sergeant at the 
checkpoint charlie crossing 
communism has crumbled in east germany the berlin wall is 
derelict and 30000 people pass through checkpoint charlie every 
day in both directions 
the fourpower agreements dividing berlin into us british and 
french sectors in the west and a soviet sector in the east remains 
in effect but berlin has been caught up in the wave of change in 
eastern europe 
for soldiers of the western allies the changes include 
canceling this years military parade and being able to visit east 
berlin in civilian clothes 
east germany has even made three new border crossings for 
western military personnel 
to air force capt janet bent of grand terrace calif and army 
staff sgt nathaniel brown of st louis mo the differences are 
important 
brown has worked at checkpoint charlie since may 1987 he has 
grim memories of the days before the wall fell in the peaceful 
revolution that ousted east germanys communist government last 
fall 
ive seen three people make escape attempts at this 
crossing and east german guards grabbed them kicked and beat 
them really got down and dirty with them he said 
now those same guards are out there smiling and waving people 
through the 39yearold sergeant said i never believed it 
would happen in my lifetime 
before the wall opened armed us patrols regularly drove along 
the barrier to monitor east german guards and possible soviet troop 
movements 
there are no more patrols brown said in an interview 
were armed as military police but about all we do is give out 
