<TEXT>
the 3000 princes of the ruling saud 
family are the cement that holds the kingdom together most experts 
agree any effective rebellion would have to be led from within the 
family 
the royal family controls every aspect of life and has remained 
united on the critical succession issue and important policy 
matters 
it has produced the arab worlds first astronaut prince sultan 
bin salman who flew on the us space shuttle discovery in 1984 
saudi arabias current rulers are descendants of king abdulaziz 
ibn saud who founded the kingdom in 1927 by conquering the desert 
tribes of the arabian peninsula 
the saud family has been largely responsible for guiding a 
tribal society of impoverished nomads into a cohesive modern state 
whose oil wealth has made it a financial superpower 
king fahd who has ruled since 1982 is believed to be the 
worlds second richest person fortune magazine estimated his 
fortune in 1988 at 18 billion the sultan of brunei is said to 
worth several billion more 
fahd has a lavishly furnished boeing 747 a 60 million yacht 
protected by stinger antiaircraft missiles and luxury homes in 
spain britain and france 
secrecy surrounds the private life of the chainsmoking monarch 
who in his youth was a playboy prince known in europes gambling 
clubs 
he is 69 the fourth son of abdulaziz to succeed his father who 
had 43 sons by 22 wives 
after crown prince abdullah 67 and defense minister sultan 
63 the succession is expected to go to the eldest of 20 younger 
brothers who is considered able 
the last son of abdulaziz sons will have the job with his inner 
circle of princes called those who tie and untie of selecting 
the eldest most respected from among the hundreds of male 
grandchildren 
family members who break the rules are dealt with quickly and 
firmly 
one of fahds younger brothers prince mishari then 19 was 
imprisoned in 1951 after shooting the british viceconsul in jiddah 
to death while drunk 
in 1965 when king sauds regime was discredited by widespread 
corruption and the kings profligate and irrational decisions the 
family supported his overthrow in favor of the respected faisal 
after faisal was assassinated by a deranged nephew on march 25 
1975 the crown passed quietly to khaled fahds halfbrother the 
nephew was beheaded khaled died in june 1982 
the only significant independent move against a saudi ruler 
since the state was founded occurred under king saud 
a group of his younger brothers critical of his misrule were 
influenced by egypts revolutionary leader gamal abdel nasser 
led by prince talal they organized the free princes 
movement to dump saud and create a constitutional monarchy the 
movement failed and the princes were exiled in 1962 
prince turki another of fahds brothers was fired as deputy 
defense minister in 1978 for drunkenness and an embarrassing 
marriage to the daughter of mohammed alfassi a doctor 
alfassi relatives used turkis money to buy a hollywood 
mansion which was then painted lime green they shocked even 
californians by highlighting the sexual organs of classical 
statuary in bright orange 
