1778 a barrel by comparison the nearmonth contract for wti 
settled at 2420 on jan 22 
the average price of a basket of seven crude oils monitored by 
opec was 1712 a barrel in the first week of april off from 
1726 in the last week of march and below the cartels minimum 
reference price of 18 a barrel 
stocks are very high opec has been producing too much for too 
long and the obvious reaction was that prices have to fall 
clayton said 
the cartels production last week came to just over 245 million 
barrels a day well over opecs cap of 221 million barrels a day 
for the januaryjune period estimated peter gignoux director of 
the international energy department at shearson lehman hutton in 
london 
it will be quite difficult to think of some mechanism by which 
they can reduce output pyne said no member country is willing 
to take on the burden he said 
in the nearterm there will be continual soft outlook for the 
markets pyne said but demand should start to pick up in early 
may he said 
