<TEXT>
when american appliance king whirlpool corp 
wanted to expand into europe as part of a strategy to dominate the 
world market it ran into the business version of a rough spin 
cycle 
the company found that although its name was a household world 
in the united states few europeans had heard of or could even 
pronounce the brand its big and american identity was no selling 
point either 
so whirlpool sought a kindred spirit on this side of the 
atlantic 
by entering a joint venture with the dutch electronics giant nv 
philips and adopting a paneuropean marketing strategy whirlpool 
may provide a valuable lesson for other us companies hoping to 
get inside the trade barrierfree europe planned for the end of 
1992 
our ultimate goal by the end of this century is to emblazon 
the whirlpool brand supreme around the world jan karel managing 
director of the joint venture told a convention of appliance 
dealers in france in january 
early last year whirlpool acquired a 53 percent stake in 
philips major domestic appliance business for 470 million it 
makes whirlpool the worlds no 1 maker of major domestic 
appliances the company says and gets it into the european market 
of 320million consumers without having to start from scratch 
whirlpool based in benton harbor mich had 4 billion in 
annual sales but none in europe it obtained instant access to 
philips 2 billion worth of european domestic appliance sales 
the joint venture called whirlpool international bv is based 
in comerio italy and employs 14000 people it has become the 
first company to sell a single brand of domestic appliances across 
europe an appliance market highly fragmented with a range of brand 
names and varying standards 
under the agreement whirlpool can use the philips brand name 
until the end of the decade 
after a year of research and development whirlpool has decided 
to use the name philips whirlpool and will gradually drop the name 
philips one country at a time 
whirlpool is virtually unknown said derek smith editor of 
the british weekly electrical and radio trading frankly i cant 
think of what else they would have done given that philips is a 
wellestablished brand in europe and the uk particularly 
whirlpool has had past success with what is known in the 
industry as transitional dual branding 
during the 1950s it acquired the air conditioning and electric 
stove businesses of radio corporation of america and called these 
products rca whirlpool for 12 years before dropping the rca 
for its latest branding attempt whirlpools parisbased 
advertising agency publicis fcs international devised seven 
candidate advertising campaigns in three languages after hiring 
researchers to interview a total of more than 1000 women consumers 
in britain france austria and spain 
the research helped the company learn the common denominators 
and what to avoid 
nick mote publicis international coordinator for the account 
said it is difficult it took us a year of development to find 
the key to the door we wanted to be as broadly appealing as 
possible 
whirlpool wanted to target housewives rather than professional 
women working outside the home who are proliferating in germany 
but remain a relative novelty elsewhere in europe 
because whirlpool is hard to pronounce in spanish or french the 
company decided to go with the english pronunciation 
the researchers found that the women interviewed were skeptical 
that the companys large size would guarantee quality and they 
discovered strong antiamerican sentiment among the british and 
austrian women 
they associated american with the disposable society and not 
technology mote said 
the end result is a 100 million philips whirlpool brings 
quality to life ad campaign launched in midfebruary 
the first television ad shown in 14 european countries looks 
futuristic with a touch of magic it shows a young mother entering 
a transparent kitchen made opaque by a golden swirl the whirlpool 
name and logo are spoken and shown repeatedly with no reference to 
the united states or the companys size 
a darkhaired actress was chosen because brunettes are spread 
throughout europe and blondes arent even her outfit was a 
headache because skirts are shorter in france than spain she wore 
pants because the chosen skirt turned out too tight 
you could alienate a lot of people if you went too sexy 
said brian kennerley managing director of whirlpool uk ltd 
asked his opinion of the campaign a buyer for a major british 
department store chain said people thought that philips 
whirlpool was a product they think it is a jacuzzi or a special 
product as opposed to a brand 
the buyer who requested anonymity added it occurred to me 
that it might have been better to promote it whirlpool philips 
to avoid confusion 
whirlpool says it went with philips whirlpool because philips 
already is a wellknown name in europe 
it says the whirlpool brand is catching on more quickly than it 
had hoped there is a total acceptance kennerley said im 
not sure we need to go beyond two or three years with the dual 
name 
