retail beef prices are likely to keep rising at least through 
this month because of unusually tight cattle supplies a situation 
already reflected in record high prices for live cattle futures 
analysts say 
but prices should ease significantly toward the end of may as 
cattle placed on feedlots during the winter reach marketable 
weights 
recordbreaking cattle futures prices shared the spotlight with 
tumbling crude oil and gasoline futures prices on the nations 
commodity markets in the past week elsewhere precious metal 
prices fell and grains and soybeans were mixed 
