<TEXT>
a federal bankruptcy judge should appoint an 
outsider to take control of eastern airlines because management is 
unable or unwilling to face market realities an adviser to the 
carriers unsecured creditors testified friday 
arthur newman managing director of investment banking at 
chemical bank said he had never seen a company miss its financial 
forecasts as frequently or by such large amounts as eastern has 
newman was the first witness at a hearing in us bankruptcy 
court to consider the creditors request for the appointment of a 
special trustee to run the airline something easterns unions have 
long sought 
present in the packed courtroom were frank lorenzo chairman of 
easterns parent texas air corp and eastern president phil bakes 
who have opposed the idea of relinquishing control of the 
financially pressed airline 
joel zweibel attorney for the committee representing the 
unsecured creditors said they wanted a trustee not to liquidate 
eastern but to sell it as a going concern 
this debtor has lost an extraordinary amount of money since 
commencement of the case he told the court 
bankruptcy judge burton r lifland expressed impatience with 
eastern which has been attempting to reorganize since it entered 
chapter 11 bankruptcy proceedings more than a year ago 
the judge who repeatedly has postponed proceedings to address 
the trustee issue told the companys attorneys you people have 
been squandering the time thats been allotted to ou 
at about 7 pm friday lifland adjourned the hearing until 
monday morning newman the first of three witnesses the creditors 
planned to call was the only one to testify on friday 
in arguing for a trustee newman said the airlines management 
was unable or unwilling to face the realities that are there in 
the marketplace for eastern 
eastern plans to call eight witnesses and they are expected to 
include lorenzo and bakes it would be the first time lorenzo has 
testifed in court since the carrier filed for bankruptcy 
eastern also is asking the judge for permission to withdraw 80 
million from an escrow account for to cover second quarter 
operations a request lifland said he would consider monday 
bruce zirinsky one of easterns attorneys said the airline 
needs the cash by monday or tuesday after the hearing though 
texas air spokesman art kent said eastern has sufficient 
resources to keep flying at least through the end of the month 
pressure to appoint a trustee mounted this past week when the 
unsecured creditors voted to reject the airlines latest 
reorganization proposal and later asked the court to name a trustee 
who would sell eastern 
easterns devastating constantly expanding and unending 
losses are extremely damaging to unsecured creditors the 
creditors motion said 
before that the creditors committee had supported eastern 
throughout its 13monthlong bankruptcy proceeding and had objected 
to the unions calls for the appointment of a trustee 
the pilots machinists and flight attendants unions struck 
eastern on march 4 1989 forcing the miamibased airline into 
bankruptcy protection five days later the machinists union remains 
on strike against eastern 
the unions long have accused lorenzo of funneling eastern assets 
to parent texas air and sister carrier continental airlines 
a report by courtappointed examiner david i shapiro filed in 
early march suggested texas air had victimized eastern by 
underpaying for the airline and some of its assets by hundreds of 
millions of dollars 
eastern recently asked lifland to accelerate approval of a 280 
million payment by texas air to settle the potential claims raised 
by shapiros report 
the trustee issue prompted the collapse last spring of a 
proposed buyout of eastern by the unions and former baseball 
commissioner peter v ueberroth 
eastern came under additional pressure monday when the 
committee representing its preferred shareholders proposed a 
reorganization plan that would give the airline to the 
shareholders unsecured creditors and new managers 
it was the first competing proposal to easterns own 
reorganization plan 
eastern owes the unsecured creditors around 980 million while 
the preferred shareholders are due 680 million the airlines most 
recent reorganization plans proposed to pay the two groups only a 
fraction of what they are owed 
eastern also has about 830 million in unfunded pension 
liabilities according to the pension benefit guaranty corp a 
government agency eastern claims its liability is only 3767 
million 
