dun amp bradstreet corp said thursday it plans to 
sell three small service companies that assist publishers large 
computer users and the oil and gas industry 
the business information marketer said the planned sales are 
part of its previously announced strategy to sharpen the companys 
focus on key markets 
the three businesses which are being offered for sale 
separately had combined revenue of 200 million last year and were 
said to be profitable 
they are 
neodata services based in boulder colo a leading provider 
of subscriptionfulfillment services for more than 270 publications 
zytron based in menlo park calif a company that transfers 
data generated by large computer users onto microfilm and 
microfiche 
petroleum information based in littleton colo which 
publishes information on drilling production and natural gas 
transportation for the oil and gas industries 
the company said the absence of operating income from the three 
subsidiaries is expected to be offset by investing and redeploying 
the cash proceeds from the sales 
while all these are profitable businesses we believe that it 
is in the best interests of dampbs shareowners to simplify dampbs 
business mix and focus our investments and resources on those key 
markets in which dampbs participation and leadership positions are 
strongest charles w moritz chairman and chied executive said 
